author: Gisele L. Pappa and Alex Alves Freitas and Celso A A Kaestner
title: AMultiobjective Genetic Algorithm for Attribute Selection
venue: Computing Laboratory Pontificia Universidade Catolica do Parana University of Kent at Canterbury
window: none of the MOFSS-found solutions were dominated by the baseline solution (the set of all attributes). In general, MOFSS found more solutions than the GA, except in the Vehicle data set. In 2 data sets (Arrhytmia and Crx) the majority of solutions found by MOFSS dominate the baseline solution. However, in the other 4 data sets the majority of solutions found by MOFSS are neutral.
